In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 8, 2011, as Mother's Day in the United States. He acknowledges the challenges faced by women raising families, including caring for elderly parents, working multiple jobs, being single parents, or serving in the military. The President emphasizes the important roles and responsibilities of mothers in our society and the love and dedication they show to their children and families. He praises the sacrifices made by mothers throughout history and highlights initiatives his administration has taken to support families, such as creating jobs, enforcing equal pay laws, and providing access to healthcare and childcare. The President urges all Americans to express their love, respect, and gratitude to mothers and to observe Mother's Day with appropriate programs and activities.